* Check out "memory files": http://docs.python.org/lib/module-StringIO.html

* Debian package:
 Hint for preinst, this will append the section to end of the file:
  sed -e '$s/$/\n\n##TIMEKPR START\n##TIMEKPR END/' file.conf
 Hint for postrm (just on purge or remove too?) removal, this removes the section timekpr would create:
  sed -e '/^## TIMEKPR START/,/^## TIMEKPR END/d' file.conf
